    "body": "Mention in the rationale section a recently proposed [alternative](https://gnusha.org/pi/bitcoindev/f97afcc5-54ba-4284-8e9b-e8c35c7101f6n@googlegroups.com/) to invalidating 64-byte transactions. Narrow the claim that invalidating 64-byte transactions fixes the vulnerability without requiring SPV verifiers to implement a workaround: it is possible to come up with [esoteric constructions](https://gnusha.org/pi/bitcoindev/178b550d-841f-43d6-8c4f-67e909cc17bfn@googlegroups.com/) that would expect an SPV proof for 64-byte transactions and would need to be patched, so it can't be claimed generally.",
    "labels": [
